an Publishing House 2010 p. 24, citing <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./N.J._Dawood" title="N.J. Dawood" id="mwA2U" class="mw-redirect">N.J. Dawood</a>'s judgement.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-4" id="cite_note-4"><a href="./Quran#cite_ref-4" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-4" class="mw-reference-text">Alan Jones, <i id="mwA2Y">The Koran</i>, London 1994, <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt19" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"ISBN","href":"./Template:ISBN"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"1842126091"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA2c"/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" about="#mwt19" id="mwA2g">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" about="#mwt19" id="mwA2k"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/1842126091" title="Special:BookSources/1842126091" about="#mwt19" id="mwA2o">1842126091</a>, opening page.<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r856303468" about="#mwt20" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"quote","href":"./Template:Quote"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"\"Its outstanding literary merit should also be noted: it is by far, the finest work of Arabic prose in existence.\""}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA2s"/><blockquote class="templatequote" about="#mwt20" id="mwA2w">"Its outstanding literary merit should also be noted: it is by far, the finest work of Arabic prose in existence."
</blockquote></span></li><li about="#cite_note-5" id="cite_note-5"><a href="./Quran#cite_ref-5" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-5" class="mw-reference-text">Arthur Arberry, The Koran Interpreted, London 1956, <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt21" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"ISBN","href":"./Template:ISBN"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"0684825074"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA20"/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" about="#mwt21" id="mwA24">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" about="#mwt21" id="mwA28"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/0684825074" title="Special:BookSources/0684825074" about="#mwt21" id="mwA3A">0684825074</a>, p. 191.<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r856303468" about="#mwt22" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"quote","href":"./Template:Quote"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"\"It may be affirmed that within the literature of the Arabs, wide and fecund as it is both in poetry and in elevated prose, there is nothing to compare with it.\" "}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA3E"/><blockquote class="templatequote" about="#mwt22" id="mwA3I">"It may be affirmed that within the literature of the Arabs, wide and fecund as it is both in poetry and in elevated prose, there is nothing to compare with it." 
